  "tips": [
    ["\ud83e\ude79","Hip / tendon \u2014 priority now","#F2554D","Pain has shifted toward the front of the hip and shows at rest in the mornings \u2014 two signals to stop self-managing and get assessed. Keep loading light until a physio sees it. The plan keeps; the hip is the priority. None of this block's value is lost by taking a week or two to sort it."],
    ["\ud83c\udfcb\ufe0f","Monday leg strength","#E06BD6","Placed after Sunday's long run as active recovery that builds resilience. Progresses rehab \u2192 build \u2192 power \u2192 maintenance. Hip thrusts (swapped in for glute bridges) and calf work are the running-specific links \u2014 but all loaded leg work pauses until the hip is assessed."],
    ["\ud83c\udf9a\ufe0f","Easy means easy","#34D399","Cap easy runs near 140 bpm. Your Strava showed easy pace drifting \u2014 discipline here is what lets the quality sessions land."],
    ["\u26a1","Strides twice a week","#9B7CF0","6\u00d7100m after two easy runs in the speed phase. Big neuromuscular gain, low load, gentle on grass."],
    ["\ud83c\udf4c","Fuel the long ones","#F59E42","Gel every ~40 min on runs 16km+. Train the gut now so race day isn't a surprise."],
    ["\ud83d\udd01","If you miss a session","#F2554D","Miss one run: skip it. Miss 3+ days: resume at the current week's start. Miss a week: repeat the prior week. Consistency beats heroics."],
    ["\u26f3","Golf / cycling / swimming","#34D399","Golf = your Thursday cross-train (10\u201314km walking). Cycling = aerobic, zero tendon load; long rides replace a run. Swimming = ideal, zero impact, any day."],
    ["\ud83d\udcca","Adjusting as you go","#F59E42","A starting structure, not a contract. As Strava comes in I'll tighten paces \u2014 especially after the Wk 10 & 16 races."],
    ["\ud83c\udfc1","Race day strategy","#4F8FF0","First 5km @ 4:13 \u2014 should feel easy. Settle to 4:11. Strong at 16km? Push. Negative splits win half marathons."]
  ]
